<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-82-0318 </DOCNO><TEXT>Radioactive waste management in the U.K. is discussed with respect tothe U.K. Waste Management Policy and the Nirex Programme. The U.K. WasteManagement Policy is outlined for the period 1976-87. This included thesetting-up of NIREX, whose remit was to implement government strategyfor the disposal of low- and intermediate-level radioactive waste. Thepresent policy, as from May 1987, is to develop a deep repository forboth low- and intermediate-level wastes. The NIREX programme includes:design studies on repository concepts, work on the behavior of a givenrepository and site and the development of waste packaging and transportsystems. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>